name: ReadOn
tweet: Why?  Stock splits make stocks affordable, so liquidity and trading volume increase.  Plus, for US companies, this allows them to be included in the Dow Jones which does not add high-priced stocks.  Even Berkshire Hathaway has split its Class B stocks.

name: ReadOn
tweet: This is exactly what CEO Warren Buffett does not want.  Buffett wants long term investors like him to invest in Berkshire Hathaway.  Not those looking to make a quick buck.
